      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "It can be frustrating and disheartening to feel like you're constantly trying to repair or fix things that seem irreparably broken. Sometimes, recognizing that you can't control everything and that external circumstances may be contributing to the chaos can be liberating. It's essential to remember that you can't pour from an empty cup; taking care of yourself and acknowledging your own limitations may be the most effective step forward. Allow yourself to acknowledge your frustration and take a step back to reassess what's truly within your control.",
      "source": "target",
